author: Aila Slisco
title: Stress Over Catching Coronavirus Is Highest Among People Between 30 and 59 Years Old, Study Says
description: Although overall worries about catching the virus have lessened since COVID-19 lockdown measures were implemented, people aged 30 to 59 are the group who remain most concerned, according to a new study.
content:
New research suggests that people aged 30 to 59 are experiencing the greatest levels of anxiety over fears that they may catch the coronavirus.
